00:09:47.300 --> 00:09:49.300
and then head off to the auction house.

00:09:49.300 --> 00:09:51.300
What is this, baloney?

00:09:51.300 --> 00:09:53.300
Oh, we were all out of watercress.

00:09:53.300 --> 00:09:55.780
Clarissa?

00:09:55.780 --> 00:09:56.780
Ferguson?

00:09:56.780 --> 00:09:58.780
This is Piper.

00:09:58.780 --> 00:09:59.780
Hi.

00:09:59.780 --> 00:10:00.780
Hey.

00:10:00.780 --> 00:10:04.090
You're Piper?

00:10:04.090 --> 00:10:06.090
She's Piper.

00:10:06.090 --> 00:10:08.090
Velasco was your mother's son of you.

00:10:08.090 --> 00:10:10.090
You were still in pigtails.

00:10:10.090 --> 00:10:12.090
My mom sent you pictures of me.

00:10:12.090 --> 00:10:15.090
She's so whatever.

00:10:15.090 --> 00:10:16.090
Cool shoes.

00:10:16.090 --> 00:10:17.090
Oh, thanks.

00:10:17.090 --> 00:10:19.090
Yeah, I myself prefer Esquidrills.

00:10:19.090 --> 00:10:21.090
Top-siders, penny-loopers.

00:10:21.090 --> 00:10:24.090
Sounds like an any-bower catalog.

00:10:24.090 --> 00:10:26.090
Whatever.

00:10:26.090 --> 00:10:28.090
Whatever turns you on.

00:10:28.090 --> 00:10:30.090
Right, Marshall?

00:10:30.090 --> 00:10:32.090
Hey, different strokes for different folks.

00:10:32.090 --> 00:10:34.090
That's what we used to say.

00:10:34.090 --> 00:10:36.090
Oh, Piper, do you want to call your mom

00:10:36.090 --> 00:10:37.090
